CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 19, 1945, pg. 14, reads: "They Said 'I Do' - Miss Hattie Fordham, niece of Mrs. Annie Jackson became the bride last Thursday of William Norman Banks, son of Mrs. Henrietta Daugherty Banks, in Grace Memorial Church. Plans for the honeymoon were not announced. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bride Hattie Fordham Banks wearing dress with ruched bodice and sweetheart neckline, and groom William Norman Banks wearing double breasted pinstriped suit, posed in Harris Studio
